## 3. Project-Specific Rules

### 3.1 File & Folder Conventions
- Follow the exact structure in `universal-science-discovery-repo-blueprint.md`
- All scientific content lives in `disciplines/`, `unknowns-catalog/`, `hypotheses/`
- All code lives in `code/`
- Schemas live in `schemas/` (use Pydantic models + YAML)
- Templates live in `templates/`

### 3.2 YAML & Data Rules
- Every YAML file must validate against its Pydantic schema.
- Use `id` fields that are stable and human-readable (e.g., `h-quantum-gravity-2026-042`).
- Always include `created`, `last_updated`, `author`, and `evidence_links`.
- Hypotheses must have clear `status`, `priority`, `impact_score`, and `proposed_tests`.

### 3.3 Legal & Ethical Guardrails (Critical)
- **Never** suggest or generate code that would download or host full-text paywalled papers.
- Always check license status before ingesting external content.
- AI-generated hypotheses or summaries must be clearly labeled as "AI-assisted" in metadata.
- If a task involves sensitive or dual-use research areas, add explicit warnings and suggest ethics review.

